<br>
100 Million Dead from Killer Asteroid!<br>
<br>
While asteroid impacts do pose a threat to Humanity, just how many human beings died from an asteroid in the 20th Century? A big fat whopping number of 0. <br>
Far worse then the threat of asteroid impacts is the death, destruction and misery that Humans have suffered at the hands of totalitarian governments. <br>
Over 100 million people were killed by their own governments in the 20th Century alone. <br>
This is exactly why we need a vigorous free-enterprise capitalist system that knows no boundaries to get us off this planet and on to colonizing the other worlds in our solar system. The American West wasn’t settled by scientists and neither will space. We need the freeing up of our creative talents and people from the heavy layers of red tape imposed by the various governmental institutions that are increasingly choking the lifeblood of American progress. <br>
The point that I am trying to make here, is that unless you have things straightened out down here first (in terms of government &amp; social aspects) we are not going to be able to deflect that killer asteroid when it does come. Instead we’ll be lucky to have three guys skimming the peach fuzz of earth in a tin can (ISS) making repairs.<br>
<br>
And then, as that large asteroid does indeed smash into the Earth spreading deadly dust, fires and tidal waves in its wake, the hippie will be taking one last bite of his granola bar, the Leftist druggie smokes his last breath of weed, the Socialist politician closes his briefcase for the last time, the Communist agitator puts down his book on Karl Marx for the final time, the Environmental Extremist wonders how nature can be so mean, the Leftist lawyer feels guilty on the injustice he perpetrated his entire career, the Anarchist throws his last brick through a store window, the soccer Mom looks up into the sky and suddenly regrets having ever joined Greenpeace and a young innocent child will never know how he was deprived life by members of his own species, who through ignorance and blindness closed the frontier of space before it could even be opened. <br>
